<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h2 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Rounding Off Numbers</h2>
</div>

<p>
<strong>Round off</strong> is the system of finding an approximate value of a number. 
It involves approximating numbers to significant figures (s.f.), 
decimal places (d.p.) or nearest whole numbers.
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>General Rounding off Rules</h3>
</div>
Generally in the rounding off system;
<br>
If a number is greater than or equal to <b>5</b> i.e. 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, the number will be <strong>rounded up </strong>
(changed to <b>1</b> and be added to the integer before it).
<br>
If a number is less than <b>5</b> i.e. 4, 3, 2, 1, the number will be <strong>rounded down</strong> (discarded or thrown away).
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Significant Figures (s.f.)</h3>
</div>
<strong>Significant Figures:</strong>  counting from the first non-zero digit at the left of a number.
<br>
<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col border-right border-danger">
    <b>Example 1</b>
    <br>
    645.63 => 600 to <strong>1 s.f.</strong>
    <br>
    645.63 => 650 to <strong>2 s.f.</strong>
    <br>
    645.63 => 646 to <strong>3 s.f.</strong>
    <br>
    645.63 => 645.6 to <strong>4 s.f.</strong>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
    <b>Example 2</b>
    <br>
    9.0397 => 9 to <strong>1 s.f.</strong>
    <br>
    9.0397 => 9.0 to <strong>2 s.f.</strong> (<strong>Note: zero after decimal is significant</strong>)
    <br>
    9.0397 => 9.04 to <strong>3 s.f.</strong>
    <br>
    9.0397 => 9.040 to <strong>4 s.f.</strong>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br>
  <b>Example 3</b>
  <br>
  0.00635 => 0.006 to <strong>1 s.f.</strong>
  <br>
  0.00635 => 0.0064 to <strong>2 s.f.</strong>

<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Decimal Places</h3>
</div>
