<br>
<strong>Solution</strong> 
<br>
12.5 litres = 12.5 x 1000 =12500ml
<br>
<strong>The number of cups of water in the tank</strong> = 12500/320 = 39.06 ~ <strong>39 cups</strong>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Estimation of Numbers</h3>
</div>
<strong>Estimation</strong> means to find a rough or approximate value of a number. 
Estimation can be <strong>surplus</strong> or <strong>deficit</strong>.
<br>
<strong>Surplus</strong> means more than the expected estimation, 
while <strong>deficit</strong> means less than the expected estimation.
<br>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
 A private school has 28 classes; one of the classes has 32 pupils. Estimate the number of pupils in that school to the nearest whole number.
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>
Number of pupils = Number of classes x Number of pupils.
<br>
= 28 x 32 
<br>
= 896 <strong>~ 900</strong>
<br>
<strong>Example 2</strong>
<br>
